::'''Lamina:''' Ah... it's you, (Trailblazer). Long time no see. What can I help you &mdash; Ah, sorry, I sometimes still revert to my old secretary mode.
::'''Lamina:''' I don't need to play the role of that man's personal secretary anymore. It takes a bit of time to adjust, but I know I'll get better at it.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It feels like you're a lot more energized than before.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500209304-->
:::'''Lamina:''' I did have some difficulties at first. After all, it was kind of hard to re-position myself when such a busy work schedule just suddenly stopped.
:::'''Lamina:''' But I soon realized many previous Capote fans were in the same boat as me. We all felt a part of our lives was forcibly taken from us, and we can't help but feel empty.
:::'''Lamina:''' So, we banded together and met up frequently to talk about our lives and work. Now everyone feels much better.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How does life feel nowadays?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500209308-->
:::'''Lamina:''' Feels... "new," I guess?
:::'''Lamina:''' I did have some plans for self-development when I first arrived at the space station, but those plans were all worn away during my time working as Capote's secretary.
:::'''Lamina:''' Now that I'm free, I feel like I'm a newcomer at the space station once again. Everything seems so new and the future is so full of possibilities.
